# release-please owns these files' serialization. Its JSON updater rewrites them
# with JSON.stringify (arrays always expanded), which prettier then wants to
# collapse when a line fits in printWidth — so the release PR's format:check goes
# red on the version bump and needs a manual re-collapse every release. Leaving
# them to release-please (as with CHANGELOG.md) removes that recurring conflict.
